WEBVTT

00:08.475 --> 00:11.378
[RAIN PATTERING]

00:13.413 --> 00:16.316
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

00:25.725 --> 00:29.562
[GRUNTING]

00:30.830 --> 00:32.032
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:12.705 --> 01:13.640
SIMON: Hank!

01:16.976 --> 01:18.111
Dad?

01:19.345 --> 01:20.580
Dad?

01:20.613 --> 01:22.048
SIMON: Hank, I need you.

01:22.081 --> 01:23.316
Dad, I'm right here!

01:23.649 --> 01:24.651
Hank!

01:25.618 --> 01:27.620
Hank!

01:25.618 --> 01:27.620
Dad?

01:27.653 --> 01:30.022
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:30.056 --> 01:31.591
Wait, please!

01:33.092 --> 01:34.894
[PANTING]

01:34.927 --> 01:36.729
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:39.465 --> 01:41.167
[METAL RATTLING,
GLASS SHATTERING]

01:41.901 --> 01:43.336
[GASPING]

01:48.508 --> 01:49.609
[GRUNTING]

01:50.643 --> 01:52.178
[SHOUTING]

01:54.547 --> 01:55.915
[SCREAMING]

01:55.948 --> 01:57.117
[GLASS SHATTERING]

02:00.986 --> 02:02.087
[GRUNTS]

02:02.121 --> 02:03.690
[GASPING]

02:03.723 --> 02:06.192
No, no, no, no!

02:06.559 --> 02:08.828
[GASPING]

02:17.904 --> 02:20.473
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

02:25.177 --> 02:27.380
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

02:34.854 --> 02:37.257
[SAW SCRATCHING]

02:39.125 --> 02:41.427
[HAMMER PINGING]

02:50.136 --> 02:52.204
Hey, guys, um,

02:52.238 --> 02:53.939
I can help
with the framing.

02:53.973 --> 02:56.041
I used to
build shit for...

02:56.075 --> 02:57.210
Or, uh, sorry.

02:57.243 --> 02:58.344
I used to build stuff
with my dad.

02:58.377 --> 03:00.112
Like, I built a...
a deck once.

03:00.146 --> 03:01.146
I-I, like...

03:01.180 --> 03:03.483
When you speak,
you do no work.

03:23.402 --> 03:24.804
Would you like coffee?

03:24.837 --> 03:27.406
Oh, yeah, sure, I'd...

03:27.440 --> 03:29.775
I'd love some.
I didn't know you guys
drank coffee.

03:29.809 --> 03:31.511
[CHUCKLES] Thank you.

03:33.145 --> 03:35.448
I'm Lucas.

03:33.145 --> 03:35.448
Susannah!

03:40.954 --> 03:42.555
I'm Susannah.

03:51.130 --> 03:54.199
Lucas, come with me.

03:54.233 --> 03:56.803
But, um, I'm working.

03:57.236 --> 03:58.705
They can wait.

04:15.854 --> 04:17.624
These were Amos'. [SNIFFS]

04:19.825 --> 04:22.395
I let them out a bit,
hoping they might fit you.

04:22.428 --> 04:25.365
You need appropriate clothes
for Vespers this evening.

04:28.000 --> 04:29.368
Try this. [SNIFFLES]

04:29.402 --> 04:31.271
See how it fits.

05:14.080 --> 05:16.082
Study Matthew 5:30.

05:23.722 --> 05:24.857
[PHONE BEEPS]

05:23.722 --> 05:24.857
THOMAS: My insurance

05:24.890 --> 05:26.658
doesn't recognize
domestic partnerships,

05:26.692 --> 05:30.295
so even if we filed...
[CLICKS TONGUE]

05:30.329 --> 05:31.731
What are we gonna do?

05:33.799 --> 05:36.268
Oh, my God.

05:33.799 --> 05:36.268
Hey, come on.

05:36.302 --> 05:37.670
You know what?

05:38.604 --> 05:39.905
We're gonna
get through this.

05:39.938 --> 05:42.308
The most important thing
is just to get you healthy.

05:42.341 --> 05:44.143
Yeah, but I can't just
sit here, you know?

05:44.176 --> 05:45.645
I-I gotta...

05:47.145 --> 05:48.347
[SIGHS]

05:48.380 --> 05:50.416
Okay, well, you know,
let's just get married.

05:50.449 --> 05:53.686
You and Henry would be
on the policy next month.
[SNAPS FINGERS]

05:53.719 --> 05:55.754
Thomas...

05:53.719 --> 05:55.754
I know. It's crazy.

05:55.788 --> 05:56.722
Yeah, kind of.

05:56.755 --> 05:58.825
I mean, it's not that crazy,
'cause I love you.

05:59.892 --> 06:01.794
We've only been together
for seven months.

06:01.827 --> 06:05.131
Very true.
Seven months and three days.

06:05.164 --> 06:07.367
And we have been
tested enough.

06:09.134 --> 06:10.436
You know
that I love you.

06:10.469 --> 06:13.972
And you know
that if I was to ask,

06:14.006 --> 06:15.641
like, really ask...

06:15.674 --> 06:17.043
I'd do it with
a lot more hoo-hah.

06:17.976 --> 06:19.077
Hoo-hah?

06:19.111 --> 06:21.581
Oh, glitz, glamour.

06:21.614 --> 06:25.183
It wouldn't be over
shitty medical bills,
you know?

06:25.217 --> 06:26.518
Way more romantic
than that.

06:26.552 --> 06:29.489
Yeah, you make
foil llama swans.

06:29.522 --> 06:30.656
I do. [CHUCKLES]

06:30.689 --> 06:32.291
I do.
I do do that.

06:32.325 --> 06:33.493
Listen, Cleo,

06:34.593 --> 06:36.462
I am certain about us.

06:42.167 --> 06:44.270
The thing is,
I'm just, um...

06:44.303 --> 06:46.171
I'm not sure I can
get married again.

06:46.204 --> 06:47.740
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

06:49.108 --> 06:50.710
Hi.

06:49.108 --> 06:50.710
Hey.

06:51.177 --> 06:52.311
THOMAS: Hey.

06:52.344 --> 06:53.879
CLEO: Are you sure
you're up for school today?

06:53.913 --> 06:54.814
HENRY: Yeah.

06:54.847 --> 06:58.017
Are you up for me
going to school today?

06:58.951 --> 07:00.285
'Cause I could stay here.

07:00.319 --> 07:01.920
Yes, yes.

07:01.954 --> 07:03.555
You go. Learn.

07:03.589 --> 07:04.857
You know what?
Jenna's gone.

07:04.891 --> 07:06.091
I'll give you a ride.

07:06.125 --> 07:07.860
Okay, yeah. Thanks.

07:08.360 --> 07:09.862
I love you.

07:13.566 --> 07:15.168
I love you, too.

07:17.002 --> 07:18.571
Bye.

07:21.841 --> 07:24.944
[RELAXING MUSIC PLAYING
OVER PHONE]

07:30.749 --> 07:33.486
[LINE CLICKS]

07:30.749 --> 07:33.486
MAN:<i> Thank you so much
for holding.</i>

07:33.519 --> 07:36.488
Hi, yes,
this is Officer Hulce

07:36.522 --> 07:38.290
from the Reston
Sheriff's Department.

07:38.324 --> 07:39.859
I'm calling to verify
a few details

07:39.892 --> 07:42.060
on an agent you have
in the field here,

07:42.094 --> 07:43.462
Ken Davidson.

07:43.495 --> 07:45.464
How long
has he been with you?

07:45.497 --> 07:49.201
Well, it looks like
he's been here

07:49.235 --> 07:51.037
for about 11 years.

07:52.405 --> 07:54.306
Huh.

07:54.339 --> 07:57.977
And it doesn't say
on his card which office
he's based out of.

07:58.010 --> 07:59.111
Is he local?

07:59.144 --> 08:03.549
Uh, he spent a few years
in our Akron offices,

08:03.582 --> 08:07.853
and then he was transferred
to our tristate offices.

08:07.886 --> 08:10.956
<i> Anything beyond that
is privileged.</i>

08:07.886 --> 08:10.956
[MICROWAVE BEEPS]

08:10.989 --> 08:13.392
And if I wanted a list
of his other clients...

08:13.425 --> 08:15.527
[GROANS]
Can you give me that?

08:15.561 --> 08:18.865
Uh, that's a question
for our legal department.

08:20.366 --> 08:22.467
Okay. Thank you.

08:22.501 --> 08:24.504
MAN:<i> No problem.</i>

08:22.501 --> 08:24.504
[LINE CLICKS]

08:28.340 --> 08:29.809
[LINE RINGING]

08:30.409 --> 08:31.577
We've got a problem.

08:31.611 --> 08:32.712
NIKOLAI: Okay.

08:32.745 --> 08:34.580
<i> A sheriff just called
asking about you,</i>

08:34.614 --> 08:36.014
<i> Anna Hulce.</i>

08:36.048 --> 08:37.349
Hmm.

08:37.382 --> 08:39.051
<i> She asked
a lot of questions...</i>

08:39.085 --> 08:41.220
<i> and was a little
condescending,
to be honest.</i>

08:41.253 --> 08:43.756
<i> I did the best I could,
but I don't know.</i>

08:46.125 --> 08:47.626
I'll take care of it.

08:47.659 --> 08:49.595
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

08:51.564 --> 08:53.533
[TOILET FLUSHES]

08:54.700 --> 08:57.169
[PENCILS SCRATCHING]

09:11.651 --> 09:13.219
CLAY:<i> Henry.</i>

09:15.554 --> 09:17.089
<i> Henry.</i>

09:17.122 --> 09:20.025
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

09:20.059 --> 09:22.028
[ECHOING]
<i> You did this to me.</i>

09:23.195 --> 09:24.763
<i> You fucking bitch.</i>

09:24.796 --> 09:26.332
<i> You tried to kill me!</i>

09:26.365 --> 09:28.601
<i> What are you?
Henry.</i>

09:28.634 --> 09:30.102
<i> You're a goddamn monster!</i>

09:43.315 --> 09:44.249
Miss Coles,

09:44.282 --> 09:46.118
this test is 40%
of your grade.

09:46.151 --> 09:49.188
<i> ♪ Run,
Life is cold down here</i>

09:49.221 --> 09:50.656
Um...

09:51.456 --> 09:52.858
I'm good. Thanks.

09:56.962 --> 09:59.631
<i> ♪ All we gotta do is run</i>

09:59.664 --> 10:01.467
<i> ♪ Life is cold down here</i>

10:01.500 --> 10:02.702
<i> ♪ No hope round here</i>

10:02.735 --> 10:03.902
<i> ♪ My, my, my</i>

10:03.935 --> 10:05.604
<i> ♪ When the coast is clear</i>

10:05.637 --> 10:07.939
<i> ♪ All we gonna do is run</i>

10:07.973 --> 10:09.675
<i> ♪ Ain't no others saving us</i>

10:09.709 --> 10:11.977
<i> ♪ Feet on the ground
When it comes to us</i>

10:12.010 --> 10:13.678
<i> ♪ That light
Should be bathing us</i>

10:13.712 --> 10:16.515
<i> ♪ So all we gonna do is run</i>

10:16.549 --> 10:18.117
<i> ♪ Run, run ♪</i>

10:20.319 --> 10:22.822
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

10:27.893 --> 10:28.827
Jenna!

10:28.861 --> 10:30.229
What a nice surprise.

10:30.262 --> 10:32.130
How are you?

10:32.163 --> 10:33.199
I'm okay.

10:34.734 --> 10:36.034
Oh, I'm good.

10:36.068 --> 10:40.473
Just, you know,
junior year is a lot so far.

10:40.506 --> 10:42.508
You know, group still
meets on Thursdays

10:42.541 --> 10:44.476
if you ever wanna come by
and say hi.

10:44.509 --> 10:47.046
Uh, yeah, I was...
I was wondering
if that was still a thing,

10:47.079 --> 10:49.748
but I don't know.

10:49.782 --> 10:51.484
It's been a long time.

10:51.517 --> 10:53.852
Three years isn't long,

10:53.886 --> 10:56.688
and grief
is an ongoing process.

10:56.722 --> 10:59.225
It doesn't go away.
It just changes shape.

10:59.258 --> 11:01.394
I know you and your mom
were very close.

11:02.595 --> 11:03.896
PATTY: Jenna.

11:07.099 --> 11:08.466
I should go.

11:08.500 --> 11:10.536
AGUILAR: Okay,
I am here anytime,

11:10.569 --> 11:12.171
group or no group.

11:15.140 --> 11:16.275
Hey.

11:16.308 --> 11:17.776
Everything okay?

11:17.809 --> 11:19.511
Yeah, uh,
just college stuff.

11:19.545 --> 11:21.246
Okay, great,
'cause we're late
to dance committee.

11:21.279 --> 11:23.749
We're voting on themes,
and I need your vote.

11:24.883 --> 11:26.852
[UPBEAT INDIE MUSIC PLAYING]

11:40.132 --> 11:42.902
[POP MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS]

11:48.907 --> 11:51.811
Are you gonna
say anything or...

11:54.780 --> 11:57.116
You're right.
This is better.

11:57.149 --> 11:58.851
I thought you wanted
to call the shots.

12:00.519 --> 12:01.721
Fine.

12:03.589 --> 12:05.090
So what happens now?

12:05.124 --> 12:07.159
You're gonna teach me
how to control this thing,

12:07.193 --> 12:09.027
and then what?

12:09.060 --> 12:11.230
Nothing happens till
you get in the truck.

12:11.263 --> 12:13.264
I already told you
I'm not gonna do that.

12:13.298 --> 12:16.268
You want control,
you have to take control.

12:17.369 --> 12:18.571
That's what I'm doing.

12:18.604 --> 12:22.108
You need
to control yourself,
not me.

12:23.074 --> 12:24.943
So what are we
doing here?

12:24.976 --> 12:26.879
Do you just hate
eating alone?

12:32.417 --> 12:33.753
SERVER: Surf's up.

12:34.486 --> 12:36.021
[HENRY SIGHS]

12:52.504 --> 12:53.773
Wow.

12:54.173 --> 12:55.274
What?

12:55.808 --> 12:58.210
You picked this place.

12:58.244 --> 12:59.144
Reston's too small.

12:59.177 --> 13:00.846
We shouldn't be
seen together.

13:02.247 --> 13:03.449
[SNIFFS]

13:05.350 --> 13:07.319
Took me a while
to find this place.

13:07.352 --> 13:09.021
I assume that's Bill.

13:09.054 --> 13:10.523
Or was.

13:11.290 --> 13:13.392
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

13:14.559 --> 13:15.694
Where is this?

13:15.727 --> 13:17.429
Sri Lanka.

13:18.430 --> 13:19.832
Any idea why?

13:21.800 --> 13:24.002
Did you see anyone?

13:24.036 --> 13:26.839
Well, someone saw the arm
of the man you killed,

13:27.872 --> 13:29.542
then probably
got ahold of a handgun

13:29.575 --> 13:32.944
that is registered to our
good friend Bill Boone.

13:32.977 --> 13:35.915
So I need to find them
before anyone else does.

13:38.750 --> 13:40.319
How good a cop
is your friend there?

13:40.685 --> 13:41.587
Anna?

13:42.755 --> 13:44.023
Should we worry about her?

13:46.525 --> 13:48.227
She's fine.

13:48.260 --> 13:49.395
She's not a problem.

13:49.428 --> 13:51.297
Okay.

13:49.428 --> 13:51.297
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

13:55.133 --> 13:57.803
You're on your own
for a few days.

13:57.836 --> 13:59.205
Next time I see you...

14:00.906 --> 14:02.608
Should be in the garage.

14:07.379 --> 14:10.949
And you're sure
your dad doesn't have
any connection to Sri Lanka?

14:10.982 --> 14:13.385
I mean, the only thing
that I really know about him

14:13.418 --> 14:15.154
is his name, so...

14:15.187 --> 14:18.556
Oh, maybe the hacker
can help us with your dad

14:18.590 --> 14:21.193
[STAMMERS] or with Nikolai,

14:21.227 --> 14:22.894
or... or both.

14:22.927 --> 14:24.162
They haven't even
gotten back to you, Townes.

14:24.196 --> 14:26.031
How would they
tell us anything?

14:27.399 --> 14:28.334
Right.

14:34.906 --> 14:37.542
I might have something

14:37.576 --> 14:41.813
that could help that Nikolai
doesn't know about.

14:41.846 --> 14:46.051
I've been having
these dreams about my dad,

14:46.085 --> 14:49.554
but I'm going to wherever
the dream is

14:49.588 --> 14:54.692
even though what's happening
in the dream isn't real.

14:54.726 --> 14:56.262
Does that make sense at all?

14:56.295 --> 14:57.129
Yes.

14:56.295 --> 14:57.129
No.

14:57.162 --> 14:59.765
Like you're sleepwalking

14:59.798 --> 15:02.835
or sleep-teleporting
and then sleepwalking.

15:02.868 --> 15:04.636
[STAMMERS]
Yeah, I guess.

15:04.670 --> 15:06.638
Well, what did the GPS say?

15:06.672 --> 15:09.941
Uh, whatever happened
last time
scrambled the receiver.

15:09.975 --> 15:11.143
I'm trying to fix it.

15:12.277 --> 15:13.878
I'm sorry.
I-I will fix it!

15:13.912 --> 15:15.747
I just need more time.

15:15.780 --> 15:17.215
[LAUGHS] I don't...

15:17.248 --> 15:19.518
Townes, it's okay.
It's... It's fine.

15:19.551 --> 15:21.687
Yeah. Yeah.

15:21.720 --> 15:22.655
Uh...

15:26.157 --> 15:27.793
Is anyone else in the dream

15:27.826 --> 15:31.329
and any other focal points
or symbology?

15:31.363 --> 15:35.667
I mean, there's that picture
that I saw in Sri Lanka,
but that's it.

15:35.701 --> 15:38.504
And you're going back
to the same place every time?

15:40.205 --> 15:42.608
Kind of. I mean,
some things change,
but...

15:43.909 --> 15:45.510
But my dad is always there.

15:45.543 --> 15:48.880
There is precedent for
communicating through dreams.

15:48.914 --> 15:51.350
<i> Dr. Who's</i> Dream Lord,
for one.

15:51.383 --> 15:54.119
Also Hiyori Iki,
the half-phantom.

15:54.152 --> 15:57.289
I can look into
dream telepathy
and astral projection.

15:57.323 --> 15:58.556
That might help.

15:58.590 --> 16:01.426
Um, in the meantime,
the more you can find out
about your dad,

16:01.460 --> 16:02.628
the better.

16:02.661 --> 16:05.230
That's...
That's the only advantage
we have over Nikolai.

16:10.602 --> 16:11.503
[DOOR CLOSES]

16:11.536 --> 16:13.038
Do you think he's okay?

16:13.472 --> 16:14.473
No.

16:14.506 --> 16:15.741
None of us are.

16:16.808 --> 16:18.177
What?

16:16.808 --> 16:18.177
Nothing.

16:18.744 --> 16:19.712
Jenna.

16:21.714 --> 16:24.683
It's just that when my mom
couldn't understand
what was happening,

16:24.716 --> 16:26.017
she'd make up stories.

16:26.051 --> 16:28.320
Jenna, your mom
had Alzheimer's.

16:28.354 --> 16:29.221
She was sick.

16:29.855 --> 16:31.623
I'm not. I'm...

16:29.855 --> 16:31.623
I know.

16:31.656 --> 16:32.590
I'm not your mom.

16:32.624 --> 16:33.758
But you said it yourself.

16:33.792 --> 16:35.293
Don't do that.

16:35.327 --> 16:37.329
Don't use something
that I said against me.

16:37.362 --> 16:39.130
I'm not using it
against you, Henry.

16:39.164 --> 16:40.365
I'm not making up my dad.

16:40.399 --> 16:42.134
He is real,
and he is out there,

16:42.167 --> 16:43.468
and he might know something.

16:43.501 --> 16:45.203
But you're putting
so much weight on him,

16:45.236 --> 16:46.938
and what... what if
he's not what you expect?

16:46.971 --> 16:48.506
I'm so done
with this conversation.

16:46.971 --> 16:48.506
What if he's something...

16:48.539 --> 16:50.642
No, Henry...

16:48.539 --> 16:50.642
Please get out.
Jenna, leave.

16:50.675 --> 16:52.277
Leave my room, please.

17:01.920 --> 17:03.288
[CHUCKLES]

17:04.789 --> 17:07.158
CONGREGATION:
<i> ♪ When I rise</i>

17:07.191 --> 17:09.995
<i> ♪ To worlds unknown</i>

17:10.028 --> 17:12.797
<i> ♪ And behold thee</i>

17:12.831 --> 17:15.233
<i> ♪ On thy throne</i>

17:15.267 --> 17:18.136
<i> ♪ Rock of ages</i>

17:18.169 --> 17:20.772
<i> ♪ Cleft for me</i>

17:20.805 --> 17:24.008
<i> ♪ Let me hide myself</i>

17:24.042 --> 17:26.278
<i> ♪ In thee ♪</i>

17:52.970 --> 17:55.173
Together
we have lost our way.

17:55.207 --> 17:58.477
In doing so, we have
suffered many losses.

17:59.744 --> 18:02.180
If we do not
correct ourselves,

18:02.213 --> 18:05.016
more suffering
will be visited.

18:05.049 --> 18:06.585
You are not
without sin.

18:09.488 --> 18:11.623
Who better should confirm
the danger of our wrongs

18:11.657 --> 18:14.359
than one who walked
neck-deep in them?

18:16.561 --> 18:17.629
Lucas, come.

18:17.662 --> 18:19.465
[INDISTINCT MURMURING]

18:23.068 --> 18:24.736
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

18:29.641 --> 18:30.876
[MAN COUGHS]

18:38.182 --> 18:40.219
This is Lucas Boone.

18:41.519 --> 18:43.254
He has come here
to learn from us,

18:43.288 --> 18:46.291
but we must also
learn from him.

19:00.138 --> 19:01.840
Matthew 5:30.

19:03.975 --> 19:06.945
"And if thy right hand
offend thee,

19:06.978 --> 19:10.215
"cut it off
and cast it from thee,

19:10.248 --> 19:14.319
"for it is profitable for thee
that one of thy members
should perish

19:14.353 --> 19:17.656
"and not that thy whole body
should be cast into hell."

19:25.697 --> 19:26.798
My...

19:28.433 --> 19:31.170
My right hand
has offended me.

19:32.871 --> 19:35.207
Both of my hands,
actually.

19:37.776 --> 19:39.311
I haven't had...

19:42.080 --> 19:45.350
Much of a chance
to become anyone

19:45.384 --> 19:49.421
other than who
I've been up until now.

19:52.924 --> 19:54.593
My father...

19:56.728 --> 19:58.263
I trusted him.

19:59.030 --> 20:01.299
I trusted
his judgment.

20:01.332 --> 20:03.535
I trusted his reason.

20:06.972 --> 20:08.273
And I thought
that being a good man

20:08.306 --> 20:10.676
meant being a good man
in his eyes.

20:12.277 --> 20:13.812
But I was wrong.

20:17.582 --> 20:20.219
Bad things have a way
of looking right sometimes.

20:27.559 --> 20:29.728
That's not an excuse.
That's just the truth.

20:32.030 --> 20:33.565
It's worse...

20:34.632 --> 20:37.536
to not be able
to see how bad
you really are.

20:38.903 --> 20:40.706
But I see it now,

20:41.672 --> 20:45.010
and I'm cutting off
those parts for good.

20:55.553 --> 20:58.624
The first step in a recovery
is reparations.

21:01.760 --> 21:03.395
I am ashamed

21:04.195 --> 21:06.898
of Jeremiah's charge.

21:06.931 --> 21:11.637
His actions are not mine,
though I aim to right them.

21:14.806 --> 21:17.241
[ZIPPER SCRAPING]

21:17.275 --> 21:19.878
This money
will be redistributed

21:19.911 --> 21:24.249
evenly among us so we may
start over in strength.

21:24.282 --> 21:25.651
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

21:30.321 --> 21:31.757
Let us pray.

21:32.591 --> 21:33.958
HENRY: Mom?

21:33.991 --> 21:35.727
CLEO: Hey, honey.

21:35.760 --> 21:37.529
Is everything okay?

21:38.229 --> 21:39.398
Yeah.

21:43.635 --> 21:46.672
I think I wanna know more
about my dad.

21:46.705 --> 21:50.709
I know that, um, before,
I said that I didn't care.

21:50.742 --> 21:51.909
No.

21:50.742 --> 21:51.909
But I...

21:51.943 --> 21:53.244
Of course. I get it.

21:53.278 --> 21:54.880
What would you like to know?

21:55.213 --> 21:56.615
Um...

21:58.683 --> 22:01.453
Do you have any
pictures of him

22:01.486 --> 22:04.622
or, like, birthday cards
or... I don't know,

22:04.656 --> 22:08.726
something that could help me
remember what he's like?

22:08.760 --> 22:11.295
I'm sorry, I don't have
anything like that, really.

22:11.329 --> 22:12.830
I didn't... [CLICKS TONGUE]

22:12.864 --> 22:15.066
I didn't really take
anything like that with us.

22:15.100 --> 22:16.468
Oh.

22:19.804 --> 22:21.740
But after he left,

22:21.773 --> 22:24.442
I did put a box
of his stuff together,

22:24.476 --> 22:27.078
of our stuff,
and I left it with a friend.

22:27.111 --> 22:28.079
Where is it?

22:28.113 --> 22:30.248
Massachusetts.

22:30.282 --> 22:33.151
But I think she, Fran,
she probably still has it.

22:33.184 --> 22:35.486
I could call her and find out.

22:35.520 --> 22:37.589
Maybe we could take
a trip down there.

22:37.622 --> 22:39.858
You know, it's not much,
but something.

22:40.158 --> 22:41.960
Yeah.

22:41.993 --> 22:43.495
Yeah, I would...

22:44.296 --> 22:47.799
I-I need that.

22:48.066 --> 22:49.033
Okay.

22:49.067 --> 22:50.502
Then I need it, too.

22:52.503 --> 22:53.972
Do you wanna go tomorrow?

22:54.005 --> 22:55.774
[LAUGHS]

22:59.177 --> 23:00.379
Ah, thank you.

23:01.446 --> 23:02.814
[ENGINE TURNING OVER]

23:06.651 --> 23:07.819
Thank you.

23:12.457 --> 23:15.193
HENRY: Nothing
in this car works.

23:15.226 --> 23:16.461
The heat works.

23:16.494 --> 23:19.030
We can't do
a three-and-a-half-hour drive

23:19.063 --> 23:21.632
without any music.

23:21.666 --> 23:23.568
Oh, are you asking me
to sing to you?

23:23.601 --> 23:25.136
I accept. [CLEARS THROAT]

23:23.601 --> 23:25.136
No.

23:25.169 --> 23:26.738
Yes.

23:25.169 --> 23:26.738
I wasn't.

23:26.771 --> 23:31.643
<i> ♪ We've got no music
In this car</i>

23:31.676 --> 23:34.245
Can you just...

23:31.676 --> 23:34.245
<i> ♪ But we're gonna
Have some fun ♪</i>

23:34.278 --> 23:36.047
Ooh, what is this?

23:36.081 --> 23:39.117
Oh, no. No, no, no.

23:39.150 --> 23:41.386
<i>"Boomtown Gulch."</i>

23:41.419 --> 23:43.154
Look at you.

23:41.419 --> 23:43.154
[SIGHS]

23:43.188 --> 23:45.022
I mean, we're listening
to this.
That's just what we're doing.

23:45.056 --> 23:47.659
No. No, no, no, no, no.
We're not gonna
listen to that.

23:47.692 --> 23:48.993
It's basically
the same thing as me
singing to you right now.

23:49.027 --> 23:50.295
We have to listen
to this.

23:50.328 --> 23:51.997
<i> ♪ You love this song better
Than anything on there ♪</i>

23:52.030 --> 23:54.466
Can we listen to this?

23:52.030 --> 23:54.466
No, I don't want to.

23:54.499 --> 23:56.367
I don't wanna listen to it.

23:56.401 --> 23:57.502
Nope.

23:57.536 --> 23:58.637
[CD CLATTERS]

24:01.573 --> 24:04.676
HENRY: Okay, well,
mystery CD it is, then.

24:05.644 --> 24:06.845
<i> [WHAT'S UP?</i> PLAYING
ON CAR STEREO]

24:06.878 --> 24:07.946
<i> ♪ And I said</i>

24:07.979 --> 24:10.649
BOTH: [SINGING ALONG]
<i> ♪ Hey, yeah, yeah-ey-ey</i>

24:10.682 --> 24:13.318
<i> ♪ Hey, yeah, yeah</i>

24:13.351 --> 24:15.654
<i> ♪ I said hey</i>

24:16.554 --> 24:19.224
<i> ♪ What's going on</i>

24:19.257 --> 24:20.392
Oh. [LAUGHS]

24:20.425 --> 24:22.193
<i> ♪ And I said hey</i>

24:22.226 --> 24:24.929
<i> ♪ Yeah, yeah-ey-ey</i>

24:24.962 --> 24:26.030
<i> ♪ Hey</i>

24:26.064 --> 24:27.165
<i> ♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

24:27.198 --> 24:29.667
Do you think
that she gets high

24:29.701 --> 24:31.435
from the breath
that she takes
in the morning

24:31.469 --> 24:33.204
like in a yoga way?

24:33.237 --> 24:36.140
Or do you think that
she actually goes
and gets high after that?

24:36.174 --> 24:38.710
Judging from the top hat
she wears in the video,

24:38.743 --> 24:42.113
I would say...
she gets really high.

24:42.146 --> 24:44.082
There's a video
for this song?

24:44.115 --> 24:45.449
Oh, yes!

24:45.483 --> 24:47.486
How could you not know that?

24:51.156 --> 24:52.290
Thank you, mystery CD.

24:52.323 --> 24:53.458
Your time with us
was brief,

24:53.491 --> 24:56.227
but your memory
shall live on.

24:56.260 --> 24:57.696
[GROANS]

25:00.531 --> 25:02.567
I'm okay. I'm just...

25:03.401 --> 25:06.171
[GROANS] I'm so sick
of this sling.

25:08.006 --> 25:11.209
It's so nice to be out
of the house, though.

25:11.242 --> 25:12.677
Yeah.

25:13.912 --> 25:14.846
How you doing?

25:14.879 --> 25:17.916
After... everything,
are you okay?

25:19.117 --> 25:20.185
Yeah, I'm fine.

25:23.788 --> 25:25.123
Really.

25:26.390 --> 25:27.959
What about you?
Are you...

25:28.559 --> 25:29.995
Don't worry about me.

25:31.696 --> 25:33.298
What about everything else?

25:36.067 --> 25:37.101
What do you mean?

25:37.134 --> 25:38.436
I mean, you know,

25:38.469 --> 25:40.705
have you had
any more contact with Clay?

25:41.005 --> 25:43.174
Um, no.

25:43.207 --> 25:46.244
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

25:46.277 --> 25:50.515
Have you thought anymore
about maybe talking
to the police

25:50.548 --> 25:51.649
about what happened
with you guys?

25:51.682 --> 25:52.918
No, I'm not
gonna do that.

25:54.185 --> 25:56.487
I really think they
could help you, you know?

25:56.520 --> 25:58.623
Mom, how?
They can't undo it.

26:03.127 --> 26:04.563
I just... I'm...

26:07.065 --> 26:10.134
I just really
don't wanna do...

26:10.167 --> 26:12.837
I don't wanna do that.
I don't wanna
tell anyone, so...

26:16.007 --> 26:17.709
Okay.

26:19.843 --> 26:23.114
Have you heard
from Dad at all?

26:25.616 --> 26:28.019
I mean, just since...

26:25.616 --> 26:28.019
No.

26:28.820 --> 26:30.889
I would have told you
if I had.

26:31.856 --> 26:36.328
He's never tried to get
in touch with you or...

26:54.278 --> 26:56.447
[CLASSIC POP MUSIC PLAYING]

26:56.480 --> 26:58.950
[WHISPERING]
Any news on Bill yet?

26:58.983 --> 27:00.618
[WHISPERING]
Why are we whispering?

27:00.651 --> 27:02.620
Well, Bill has a lot
of enemies in this town,

27:02.653 --> 27:04.489
but he also has
a lot of friends, you know?

27:04.522 --> 27:05.623
[DOOR BELL JINGLES]

27:05.657 --> 27:06.691
Hey, Ken.

27:06.725 --> 27:08.292
Hi there, uh...

27:08.326 --> 27:09.427
Iris, is it?

27:09.460 --> 27:10.795
That's my name.

27:10.828 --> 27:13.531
Well, Iris, could I get
a cup of coffee to go?

27:13.564 --> 27:14.732
Black?

27:14.765 --> 27:15.934
IRIS: We're out
of to-go cups,

27:15.967 --> 27:17.668
so you'll have stay
if you want coffee.

27:17.702 --> 27:19.304
Well, twist my arm.

27:19.337 --> 27:20.471
I'll be right with you.

27:20.505 --> 27:22.073
Thank you.

27:25.576 --> 27:26.978
Hello, Officer.

27:27.011 --> 27:29.280
Nice to see you again.

27:27.011 --> 27:29.280
Hi.

27:29.313 --> 27:30.715
Mind if I plant here
a minute?

27:30.748 --> 27:32.717
Not at all, no.

27:34.652 --> 27:37.088
You know,
Iris is just being nice.

27:37.388 --> 27:38.456
Hmm?

27:38.490 --> 27:40.758
They don't have to-go cups
at The Yolk.

27:40.792 --> 27:42.260
There's nowhere
to go in Reston,

27:42.293 --> 27:43.661
so why stock the cups?

27:43.695 --> 27:46.230
[LAUGHS]
That's good, yeah.

27:46.264 --> 27:48.499
Took me a while to get used
to the pace around here, too.

27:48.533 --> 27:50.234
NIKOLAI: Yeah.

27:50.268 --> 27:52.937
I imagine it's, uh,
a lot slower than the city.

27:54.572 --> 27:56.240
You don't work
in the city much?

27:56.273 --> 27:57.808
Try not to.

27:57.842 --> 28:00.812
Well, that must be hard,
being on the road like this.

28:00.845 --> 28:02.781
What's it like being away
from your family?

28:03.714 --> 28:06.717
Oh, you know,
same as it is for anyone.

28:06.750 --> 28:08.620
Fun for a couple days.
Then it gets old.

28:08.653 --> 28:10.455
You planning on a long stay?

28:12.423 --> 28:13.425
Whoa.

28:15.326 --> 28:16.494
Well, this job has turned out

28:16.527 --> 28:20.765
to be a little more complicated
than usual, considering,

28:20.798 --> 28:22.400
so I'll stay as long
as I have to.

28:23.801 --> 28:26.137
Um, though
I must say, uh,

28:26.170 --> 28:29.907
I've had about enough
of the tristate.
[CHUCKLES]

28:29.940 --> 28:31.742
Hopefully Bill shows
back up again.

28:31.776 --> 28:33.712
That'd move things along
for me.

28:34.178 --> 28:35.379
Speaking of,

28:35.413 --> 28:36.347
how is all that?

28:38.049 --> 28:41.485
I'm not at liberty to comment
on the investigation

28:41.519 --> 28:42.787
since it's ongoing.

28:42.820 --> 28:44.989
[CLICKS TONGUE] Right.

28:45.023 --> 28:46.191
Of course.

28:50.094 --> 28:52.230
Well, it seems like you
have your hands full,

28:52.263 --> 28:56.033
and I... hate to be
a distraction.

28:56.067 --> 28:57.235
Um...

28:58.870 --> 29:01.506
This is my personal number,

29:01.539 --> 29:03.407
in case you need
to get in touch again.

29:03.441 --> 29:06.978
It's much easier than
going through the red tape
of the main office.

29:07.011 --> 29:10.248
Yeah, they seem a little
short-staffed around there.

29:10.281 --> 29:12.483
Website's down, too.

29:12.517 --> 29:14.552
[CHUCKLES]

29:14.585 --> 29:16.253
Well, we do our best.

29:16.287 --> 29:17.856
Mr. Davidson.

29:18.456 --> 29:20.758
Ken, please.

29:20.791 --> 29:23.428
You gave Henry Coles
your number as well.

29:23.995 --> 29:25.897
But she's just a kid.

29:25.930 --> 29:27.832
It's easy
to forget that sometimes.

29:28.699 --> 29:30.802
Yeah, well,
if I reach out to her,

29:30.835 --> 29:33.037
[STUTTERS]
I'll keep you
in the loop.

29:36.807 --> 29:39.377
Thank you, Iris.

29:42.413 --> 29:44.282
[DOOR BELL JINGLES]

29:59.564 --> 30:02.267
Hey, come sit.

30:03.568 --> 30:05.036
Um, no,
I don't wanna interrupt,

30:05.069 --> 30:07.138
and I have homework, so...

30:07.171 --> 30:08.406
Please.

30:09.140 --> 30:10.341
I miss you.

30:22.019 --> 30:23.855
I saw the VCR was out.

30:26.057 --> 30:28.526
Been watching
the wedding video, huh?

30:32.696 --> 30:34.132
Do you wanna talk about it?

30:36.100 --> 30:37.902
I...

30:37.935 --> 30:41.438
just wanted to remember
what you looked like
with a full head of hair.

30:41.472 --> 30:42.440
[CHUCKLES]

30:43.273 --> 30:46.878
Well, the tape
is up in your bedroom.

30:47.912 --> 30:49.646
So it's there
when you want it.

30:49.680 --> 30:50.882
I didn't wanna
leave it out,

30:50.915 --> 30:52.817
and I didn't wanna...

30:52.850 --> 30:54.619
I didn't wanna put it away.

30:55.652 --> 30:57.155
Thanks.

30:57.855 --> 30:59.257
Someday,

31:00.358 --> 31:02.393
you're gonna make
a wedding video
of your own.

31:02.426 --> 31:04.462
You'll look just like
your mom. [CHUCKLES]

31:05.329 --> 31:07.031
So beautiful.

31:08.633 --> 31:11.436
And whoever marries you
is gonna be the luckiest man
in the world.

31:15.706 --> 31:17.274
Yeah, um...

31:17.307 --> 31:21.279
I actually kind of
have a boyfriend.

31:22.713 --> 31:24.549
Um, I mean, I do.

31:24.582 --> 31:25.617
Zach.

31:26.918 --> 31:31.222
Um, we're not getting married
or anything, obviously,

31:31.255 --> 31:35.326
but I-I just thought
you should know
that it was happening.

31:35.660 --> 31:38.128
Wow, okay.

31:38.162 --> 31:39.730
[EXHALES]
Okay, my daughter
has a boyfriend.

31:39.763 --> 31:42.533
I don't know.
Maybe I could invite him
over for dinner sometime.

31:42.567 --> 31:44.234
What about tonight?

31:44.268 --> 31:46.237
I mean,
it's just the two of us.

31:48.272 --> 31:49.740
Sure.

31:49.774 --> 31:52.644
Yeah, I'll ask him.

31:54.578 --> 31:55.914
[SIGHS]

32:01.285 --> 32:03.488
I thought I heard you
pulling up.

32:03.521 --> 32:06.290
Hi. It's been forever.

32:06.323 --> 32:07.992
Oh, oh.

32:06.323 --> 32:07.992
Gentle. Sorry.

32:08.025 --> 32:09.927
Oh, jeez, what happened?

32:09.961 --> 32:12.163
I slipped on some ice
in the driveway.

32:12.196 --> 32:14.465
It was stupid.

32:12.196 --> 32:14.465
Oh, my God.

32:15.199 --> 32:17.936
And who's this?
Friend from work?

32:19.336 --> 32:21.205
Kidding.
I'm just kidding.

32:21.238 --> 32:24.475
Oh, my God, Henry,
look at you.

32:24.508 --> 32:25.743
Hi.

32:25.776 --> 32:30.281
Okay. Okay, come on.
Come in, come in.

32:30.314 --> 32:33.084
I found Simon's box.
I pulled it out
of the basement.

32:33.117 --> 32:35.219
We were so nervous.

32:35.252 --> 32:38.256
I mean, we had never opened
for a big band
like that before.

32:38.289 --> 32:39.256
[MELLOW ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

32:39.289 --> 32:40.658
It's Marcy Playground, right?

32:40.691 --> 32:44.161
Yes, Marcy
fucking Playground.

32:44.195 --> 32:46.096
I mean, pardon my French.

32:46.130 --> 32:47.999
No, that's okay.
Henry speaks French.

32:48.032 --> 32:48.999
FRAN: Right.

32:49.033 --> 32:51.602
So we were getting
ready for the show

32:51.636 --> 32:55.306
and we were nervous,
so we had a couple of beers
to calm ourselves down.

32:55.340 --> 32:58.076
Then after sound check,
we were getting pumped,

32:58.109 --> 33:00.077
and we thought,
"Hey, we'll have
a couple of shots."

33:00.110 --> 33:01.479
Hey, I only had one shot.

33:01.512 --> 33:02.746
FRAN: No, you lie.

33:02.780 --> 33:04.082
Mmm-mmm.

33:02.780 --> 33:04.082
Ugh.

33:04.115 --> 33:07.184
Needless to say,
we were not
asked to go on the tour.

33:07.218 --> 33:09.587
You missed the best part.

33:09.620 --> 33:11.155
We got kicked out
of the bar.

33:11.822 --> 33:12.857
What?

33:12.890 --> 33:14.257
Why?

33:14.291 --> 33:16.627
There was a fight,
capital F.

33:16.660 --> 33:18.229
CLEO: No, it wasn't that bad.

33:19.463 --> 33:22.533
Simon got into it with
one of the other band's
bass players

33:22.566 --> 33:25.035
because he thought that
that guy was hitting on me,

33:25.068 --> 33:26.404
which he was not.

33:26.437 --> 33:27.571
My dad was there?

33:27.605 --> 33:29.173
Nearly broke that guy's arm.

33:29.206 --> 33:31.109
It wasn't a big deal.

33:34.345 --> 33:36.347
Seems like a big deal to me.

33:45.790 --> 33:47.158
She okay?

33:47.491 --> 33:48.859
Yeah.

33:48.893 --> 33:50.761
She's just a teenager,
you know?

33:50.795 --> 33:52.296
Mm.

33:54.098 --> 33:56.333
Okay, I'm not trying
to suck up to you,
Mr. Hope,

33:56.367 --> 33:59.036
but this is the best lasagna
I've ever had.

33:59.069 --> 34:01.672
Nice. That's Jenna's
mom's recipe.

34:01.706 --> 34:03.907
I try my best,
but nothing compares
to Elizabeth's.

34:03.940 --> 34:05.909
No, Dad,
it's good, really.

34:05.943 --> 34:07.377
All right.

34:07.411 --> 34:09.647
Jenna's mom and I,
we were high school
sweethearts, too.

34:09.680 --> 34:10.948
Dad, let's talk...

34:10.982 --> 34:13.317
I would tape love poems
to her locker.

34:13.351 --> 34:14.385
[LAUGHTER]

34:14.419 --> 34:16.854
Oh, my God,
she actually
showed me one once.

34:16.888 --> 34:19.023
Oh? Was it good?

34:19.056 --> 34:20.124
[BOTH GROANING]

34:20.157 --> 34:21.792
Well,
they got better.

34:21.825 --> 34:23.394
They got better,
seriously.

34:23.427 --> 34:25.429
Um, if you want more,
Zach, there's tons.

34:25.463 --> 34:27.031
Yeah, that sounds great.

34:25.463 --> 34:27.031
All right, good.

34:27.064 --> 34:28.132
Oh, no, I got it.
I got it.

34:28.165 --> 34:29.734
Okay.

34:28.165 --> 34:29.734
Thank you.

34:29.767 --> 34:32.670
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

34:35.540 --> 34:37.908
I know that I'm supposed
to hate my daughter's
boyfriend,

34:37.941 --> 34:39.844
but, you know, I think
he's pretty great.

34:40.311 --> 34:41.845
Good.

34:41.878 --> 34:43.147
I'm glad.

34:55.459 --> 34:58.129
[ALARM BLARING]

34:55.459 --> 34:58.129
[SHOUTING]

34:59.931 --> 35:01.232
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

35:02.533 --> 35:03.868
Where have you been?

35:03.901 --> 35:05.936
Did you get my messages?

35:05.970 --> 35:07.572
Do you know the guy
from the picture?

35:08.940 --> 35:10.808
[TENSE MUSIC]

35:15.079 --> 35:17.682
[MELLOW ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

35:43.641 --> 35:46.277
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

36:22.979 --> 36:24.315
FRAN: Hey.

36:24.882 --> 36:26.250
How you doing in here?

36:26.817 --> 36:27.852
Fine.

36:29.953 --> 36:32.255
[SIGHS]

36:32.289 --> 36:34.692
I shouldn't have told
that story. I'm sorry.

36:35.993 --> 36:37.194
I don't know.

36:37.227 --> 36:41.666
She just, like,
never talks about him, so...

36:42.833 --> 36:44.635
Right, right.

36:44.668 --> 36:46.303
Yeah.

36:46.337 --> 36:50.774
You know, um, sometimes...

36:50.807 --> 36:55.279
the good stuff is harder
to talk about than the bad,

36:55.312 --> 36:57.949
and the bad's really hard
to talk about, you know?

36:59.016 --> 37:00.518
Did you like him?

37:00.951 --> 37:01.952
Your dad?

37:01.985 --> 37:03.187
Yeah, sure.

37:03.220 --> 37:05.155
I mean, he was great.

37:05.188 --> 37:07.324
You know, funny, sweet.

37:07.358 --> 37:11.228
Could be a little difficult
to be around towards the end.

37:11.262 --> 37:14.498
I'm sure your mom
just wants to protect you
from all that, Henry.

37:16.767 --> 37:20.404
Was he, um...

37:22.172 --> 37:25.243
Was he ever, like,
violent at all?

37:27.845 --> 37:30.881
I mean, did he ever,

37:30.914 --> 37:33.417
like, hurt her or...

37:35.619 --> 37:36.553
No.

37:36.586 --> 37:38.455
No, I'm sure
she would have told me

37:38.489 --> 37:40.090
if anything
like that happened.

37:40.123 --> 37:41.993
Yeah.

37:42.026 --> 37:44.795
But, uh, he could be
a little paranoid.

37:45.763 --> 37:47.999
Off in his own world,
you know?

37:50.301 --> 37:54.338
But hey... hey,
Thomas sounds great, right?

37:54.371 --> 37:56.841
Different from the guys
your mom used to date.

37:56.874 --> 37:58.208
Very different, yeah.

37:58.242 --> 38:00.745
Mm. So you like him?

38:03.280 --> 38:04.482
Yeah.

38:05.649 --> 38:06.817
Good.

38:06.850 --> 38:09.620
Maybe then she'll finally
get divorced and move on.

38:10.487 --> 38:12.790
You know, she deserves
to be happy.

38:35.412 --> 38:36.914
[FLOORBOARD CREAKS]

38:38.749 --> 38:40.551
Sorry, I...

39:03.373 --> 39:05.543
I imagine the barn's
been cold at night.

39:05.942 --> 39:07.677
No, it's fine.

39:07.711 --> 39:10.448
You should sleep
in here tonight.

39:11.715 --> 39:14.085
Amos' room
can be yours for now.

39:16.353 --> 39:18.089
I don't mind the barn.

39:18.889 --> 39:20.458
I insist.

39:29.300 --> 39:30.968
That's wrong.

39:33.003 --> 39:34.472
[LUCAS SIGHS]

39:35.940 --> 39:37.975
I've been praying...

39:41.312 --> 39:43.147
But I don't feel relieved
of anything.

39:48.452 --> 39:50.955
How do I know
if it's working?

39:52.489 --> 39:56.493
You must make peace
with yourself before you
can make peace with God.

39:56.527 --> 39:58.763
But I don't know
how to do that.

40:00.097 --> 40:02.600
It takes patience...

40:04.835 --> 40:05.870
And faith.

40:23.287 --> 40:25.890
Stay strong, Lucas.

40:30.160 --> 40:32.029
I have big plans
for you.

40:46.376 --> 40:48.045
You wanna talk about it?

40:58.956 --> 41:00.558
[ENGINE STOPS]

41:02.759 --> 41:05.463
Are you still married to Dad?

41:11.902 --> 41:13.838
Yes. [SIGHS]

41:17.107 --> 41:18.542
[CLICKS TONGUE]

41:19.343 --> 41:20.711
Why?

41:21.512 --> 41:24.915
And why do I not know that?

41:25.950 --> 41:27.151
I don't know.

41:28.652 --> 41:30.754
It's hard to divorce someone
who isn't there.

41:32.690 --> 41:33.556
Mom...

41:33.590 --> 41:36.026
I don't know what
you want me to say.

41:36.059 --> 41:37.227
It doesn't mean anything.

41:37.261 --> 41:38.695
That's bullshit.

41:37.261 --> 41:38.695
Henry.

41:38.729 --> 41:43.400
You've been dragging me around
from boyfriend to boyfriend,

41:43.434 --> 41:46.770
fully knowing that it's not
going to work

41:46.803 --> 41:48.505
because you're fucking married.

41:48.539 --> 41:49.840
That's not fair.

41:49.873 --> 41:51.408
I know!

41:51.442 --> 41:53.043
It's not fair.

41:53.076 --> 41:56.680
It's not fair that you keep
putting me through this shit.

41:56.714 --> 42:00.618
It is not fair that you
don't tell me anything!

42:01.218 --> 42:02.419
This is my life, too!

42:02.452 --> 42:03.787
I understand that.

42:03.820 --> 42:05.122
Do you?

42:05.889 --> 42:08.659
You didn't even
look for Dad.

42:08.692 --> 42:10.794
He was fucked up,
so you just left.

42:10.828 --> 42:13.163
You just left...

42:10.828 --> 42:13.163
He abandoned me!

42:13.196 --> 42:14.397
He abandoned us, Henry!

42:14.431 --> 42:16.266
He abandoned us.

42:16.299 --> 42:17.801
Why would I look for him?

42:17.834 --> 42:19.570
For me!

42:19.603 --> 42:22.640
You're supposed to look
for him for me!

42:23.607 --> 42:24.774
You don't remember him.

42:24.808 --> 42:26.276
You don't remember
what it was like.

42:26.310 --> 42:28.445
He made things very hard
for us.

42:28.479 --> 42:32.015
Mom, maybe he was afraid
of something

42:32.048 --> 42:34.318
and he didn't think
he could tell you or trust you.

42:34.351 --> 42:36.053
Maybe he thought you wouldn't
fucking believe him.

42:36.086 --> 42:37.454
You don't know.

42:37.488 --> 42:39.623
If he doubted me
or didn't trust me,

42:39.657 --> 42:42.292
I mean, that's...
that's on him.

42:42.325 --> 42:44.327
Talking to him,
it was like talking
to a brick wall.

42:44.361 --> 42:45.395
It's like talking to you.

42:45.428 --> 42:46.664
You won't tell me about Clay.

42:46.697 --> 42:48.065
You won't tell me
about the hospital.

42:48.098 --> 42:49.199
You won't tell me
about the shooting.

42:49.232 --> 42:50.901
I'm so s...

42:50.935 --> 42:54.238
I'm so sorry it's so hard
for you to be my mom.

42:54.271 --> 42:57.274
I'm so sorry that
so much terrible shit
has happened to me

42:57.307 --> 42:58.508
and that you have
to deal with it.

42:58.542 --> 43:01.245
You have to deal with it,
and you're not.

43:01.278 --> 43:03.146
Are you fucking kidding?

43:03.179 --> 43:05.582
Look, your father
is the one who left us,
okay?

43:05.615 --> 43:06.850
And I understand
if you want to blame me.

43:06.884 --> 43:09.119
That's not what happened.
He didn't leave.

43:13.056 --> 43:14.057
Okay.

43:14.090 --> 43:16.092
Will you please fucking
tell me what happened?

43:16.126 --> 43:19.797
Enlighten me, Henry,
because I would
really like to know.

43:27.070 --> 43:28.739
Forget it.

43:28.772 --> 43:30.274
[ENGINE TURNING OVER]

43:41.751 --> 43:43.721
I'm entitled to my pain.

43:45.655 --> 43:47.658
Everyone hurts
in a different way.

43:49.092 --> 43:51.962
And you don't get
to judge me for that.

43:51.995 --> 43:54.331
And I'm sorry
if it hurts you.

43:54.898 --> 43:56.967
I'm sorry I'm a person.

43:59.069 --> 44:02.006
And I'm dealing with it
the best way that I can.

44:06.810 --> 44:09.847
You're not
dealing with it.

44:09.880 --> 44:11.281
CLEO: Neither are you.

44:14.518 --> 44:17.021
[TRAIN HORN BLOWING]

44:18.488 --> 44:20.324
[TRAIN CHUGGING]

44:28.465 --> 44:30.334
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

44:36.140 --> 44:39.043
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

44:57.461 --> 44:58.929
[METAL CREAKING]

44:59.629 --> 45:01.765
[OBJECTS RATTLING]

45:06.336 --> 45:08.038
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

45:15.579 --> 45:17.114
[INHALES DEEPLY]

45:24.888 --> 45:26.457
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

45:48.645 --> 45:50.948
[SNIFFLES]

45:59.556 --> 46:00.991
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

46:01.024 --> 46:02.826
Terry, what do you
got for me?

46:02.860 --> 46:05.395
TERRY: (ON PHONE)<i> Yeah,
the blood sample
you gave me was ID'd.</i>

46:05.996 --> 46:08.499
<i> Came back as Bill Boone.</i>

46:09.532 --> 46:11.034
Okay.

46:12.201 --> 46:14.137
You kept that
off the books, right?

46:14.170 --> 46:16.038
<i> Of course. You don't ask
for favors, Hulce,</i>

46:16.072 --> 46:18.208
<i> so when you do,
I trust it.</i>

46:18.242 --> 46:19.509
Thanks. [LAUGHS]

46:19.543 --> 46:20.577
Okay, I gotta go.
Working.

46:20.610 --> 46:21.778
<i> Always.</i>

46:21.811 --> 46:23.147
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

46:24.347 --> 46:25.816
[BRAKES SQUEALING]

46:33.490 --> 46:34.558
[RADIO BEEPS]

46:34.591 --> 46:37.394
This is Officer Hulce
on the 40-mile mark,
Route 242.

46:37.427 --> 46:39.963
I need an ambulance and backup
to my location stat.

46:39.996 --> 46:40.964
I got a body in the road.

46:40.998 --> 46:42.800
DISPATCHER: (ON RADIO)
<i> Copy that.</i>

46:47.470 --> 46:48.738
Are you all right?

46:48.771 --> 46:50.373
You okay?

46:50.406 --> 46:52.009
[WHOOSHING]

46:57.447 --> 46:59.049
[ENGINE TURNING OVER]

47:00.584 --> 47:02.486
[ENGINE REVVING]

47:04.654 --> 47:06.023
[GUNSHOTS]

47:11.327 --> 47:13.096
[GLASS SHATTERING]

47:16.199 --> 47:17.534
[PANTING]

47:23.006 --> 47:25.408
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

47:25.441 --> 47:26.944
[CAR ALARM BEEPING]

47:35.184 --> 47:38.722
DISPATCHER: (ON RADIO)
<i> Officer Hulce, we have backup
en route to your location.</i>

47:38.755 --> 47:40.591
<i> Three minutes out.
Do you copy?</i>

47:48.698 --> 47:50.300
[WHOOSHING]

47:50.901 --> 47:53.170
[GASPING]

47:57.974 --> 47:59.576
[GROANING SOFTLY]

48:02.445 --> 48:03.580
[INJECTS]

48:58.068 --> 49:01.104
[SPEAKING LATIN]

49:13.316 --> 49:14.351
[SNIFFLES]
